  explanation = 'The most common type of punctuation in English writing, the comma, is frequently used to separate items in a series.  But when a series contains three or more items, the comma separates the last item from the first item in the series, not the first item from the last item. In this case, the verb ''separates'' is the correct answer. The verb should be in the third person singular form because it refers to ''the comma,'' which is singular. The passage states that "The most common type of punctuation in English writing, the comma, is frequently used to separate items in a series. But…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice A is correct because it aligns with that evidence: separates. This choice completes the idea as a full sentence rather than a fragment.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
